Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
violationBrowserDeleteByArea(25.10)        violationBrowserDeleteByArea(25.10)

Name
       violationBrowserDeleteByArea - Deletes markers from a specified area or
       the entire design area

Syntax
       violationBrowserDeleteByArea

       [-help]

       [-all]

       [-area {<x1 y1 x2 y2}>]

       Deletes  markers  from a specified area or the entire design area. When
       the -area and -all parameters of this command are specified at the same
       time, -all is applied.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes the type  and  default
              information for each violationBrowserDeleteByArea parameter.

              For  a  detailed  description of the command and all its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man violationBrowserDeleteByArea

       -all   Deletes markers from the entire design area.

       -area {<x1 y1 x2 y2>}
              Specifies a bounding box for the area from which to delete mark-
              ers. For example, violationBrowserDeleteByArea -area  {0  0  100
              100}.

Related Information
              * Identifying and Viewing Violations chapter of User Guide.

              * "Evaluating  Violations"  in  the  Using  the NanoRoute Router
                chapter of User Guide.

